sec.p:
The Italian unselected population of this observational multicenter study shows the following difference baseline characteristics versus the BR.218 study and TRUST study,2 respectively:


A higher median age (69 vs 62; 63);

A better performance status if we consider subgroup with PS 0–1 (78,8 vs 67,6; 75);

A higher percentage in second-line treatment (63,2 vs 50,6; 49);

No patient belonging to the Asian ethnic group, which instead formed 12.9% of the arm with erlotinib in the BR.21 Trial and 20% of the TRUST study;

A higher percentage of non-smoker patients (30.6 vs 21.3; 30).
